<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,534,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cephennium gallicum</emphasis>
Ganglbauer
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,799,1145]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
On five occasions (
<date box="[497,650,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2001-07-07">
July 
<number box="[558,650,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="7.2001">7, 2001</number>
</date>
, 
<date box="[666,837,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002-05-11">
May 
<number box="[729,837,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="11.2002">11, 2002</number>
</date>
, 
<date box="[851,1008,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002-06-09">
June 
<number box="[914,1008,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.2002">9, 2002</number>
</date>
, 
<date box="[1022,1265,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002-09-22">
September 
<number box="[1158,1265,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="22.2002">22, 2002</number>
</date>
, and 
<date box="[264,462,839,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2004-10-09">
October 
<number box="[369,462,839,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.2004">9, 2004</number>
</date>
) six specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ganglbauer" authorityName="Ganglbauer" box="[695,1104,839,865]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis box="[695,956,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cephennium gallicum</emphasis>
Ganglbauer
</taxonomicName>
were collected in Point Pleasant Park. Five specimens were collected under the bark of branches or limbs of recently fallen or damaged white pine. The sixth specimen was collected while sweep netting through heath vegetation in a small sphagnum bog. Additionally, Peter Hammond collected four specimens in the Park in July, 
<number box="[766,825,999,1025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1988.0">1988</number>
(NHM). These records represent the first report of this species in North American (
<figureCitation box="[758,871,1039,1065]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[264,368,1690,1714]" captionTargetBox="[335,1234,1225,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[320,1256,1222,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3: Cephennium gallicum Ganglbauer, Point Pleasant Park, Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Dorsal habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169605/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figures 
<number box="[856,871,1039,1065]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[929,947,1039,1065]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[264,368,1375,1399]" captionTargetBox="[411,1176,797,1361]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[344,1200,788,1367]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4: Cephennium gallicum Ganglbauer, Point Pleasant Park, Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169606/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<number box="[929,947,1039,1065]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[980,1238,1039,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis box="[980,1238,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cephennium gallicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also the only species of Palearctic scydmaenid known to have become established in North 
<taxonomicName box="[264,369,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="America" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<collectingCountry box="[264,369,1119,1145]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">America</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
